# UnoDOS/AppleII milestone-3 scheduler feasibility prototype (HANDOFF-M3 SS6).
# Build: ./build.sh sched   (assembles with -DSCHED_PROTO=1)
# Run:   python3 harness.py build/unodos_sched.dsk shots < tests/m3_sched.script
#
# Proves option 1 (stack partitioning): two tasks each own a slice of page 1,
# task_yield saves/loads S, a canary at each slice floor catches overflow.
# Expected result on screen: "STACK-PARTITION OK - canaries intact",
# switches:40, t0 depth:2 - i.e. 40 cooperative context switches completed,
# both canaries intact, the kernel's draw_string->draw_char chain fitting the
# slice with room to spare. The shipping kernel keeps option 3 (poll-and-
# dispatch) because the full-screen single-app model needs no live scheduler;
# this proto is the evidence option 1 WOULD work if it ever did.
wait 200
shot m3_sched_proto
quit
